{"type":"message","id":"dab33c24","parentId":"673a01b3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:11:34.797Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clearer picture. Let me summarize what happened in this pulse cycle based on the process log and the pulse log content:\n\n1. **OBSERVATION**: TIC Experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\n2. **ACTION**: Create `src/tic-classifier.ps1` - a Temporal Invariance Compression implementation\n3. **MUTATION**: The mutation was applied - it created a new file `src/tic-classifier.ps1` (1819 chars replacing 0)\n4. **COMMIT**: Changes were committed to the sandbox repository\n   - 7 files changed, 308 insertions(+), 98 deletions(-)\n   - Created `memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 201036.md`\n   - Created `mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 201036.mutation`\n   - Renamed the previous mutation from proposed to rejected\n\nSo the sandbox completed a pulse cycle and made meaningful progress on the TIC Experiment. \n\nThe key insight driving this work is that COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY means the causal structure underlying the sandbox's operations is fundamentally the same as its invariant structure - they're two perspectives on the same underlying architecture. The proposed classifier should validate this by measuring whether causal relationships remain consistent across sessions.","thinkingSignature":"91fff3d3e6a28c4463a56d71132af9fed4a622118d17cd0fc77bde1b2ff31add"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-23 20:10:36**\n\n**What happened this cycle:**\n\nThe sandbox committed meaningful progress on the **TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment**. Here's what was proposed, executed, and shipped:\n\n- **New file created:** `src/tic-classifier.ps1` (1,819 chars) — implements feature extraction, invariant/variant classification, and prediction accuracy measurement for the TIC hypothesis\n- **Key hypothesis being tested:** COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY — that causal structure IS invariant structure; if true, predicting what changes vs. persists across pulses is the same problem as identifying causal relationships\n- **Success targets:** >70% classification accuracy, >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\n\n**Commit summary:** 7 files changed, +308 insertions, -98 deletions — including the new classifier and the pulse session log.\n\n**One mutation was rejected** (the previous pulse's proposal, `pulse_2026-03-23 195521.mutation`, was moved to `mutations/rejected/`), meaning only the most recent proposal was accepted.\n\n**Current state:** The sandbox is positioned to run the TIC classifier against historical pulse logs (`logs/pulse_*.md`) to validate whether invariants truly predict future state — the core empirical test of the duality hypothesis."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5842,"output":551,"cacheRead":11878,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18271,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774311082573}}
